e stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan Treiago was born about 1346, in Tregothnan, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, her father, Stephen Treiago, was 28 and her mother, Joan Cheynduit, was 20. She married John Trenoweth about 1370, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1400, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"Abt 1346–1400":"umbes 1346–1400","1346–1400":"1346–1400","1358–Female":"1358–Surnud","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","1365–1427":"1365–1427","1366–Female":"1366–Surnud","1380–1443":"1380–1443","1320–1400":"1320–1400","1327–1400":"1327–1400","about 1380":"umbes 1380","Abt 1346":"umbes 1346","1380":"1380","ABT 1370":"umbes 1370","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1358":"1358","1346":"1346","1400":"1400","1443":"1443","1366":"1366","1365":"1365","1320":"1320","about 1365":"umbes 1365","about 1366":"umbes 1366","about 1344":"umbes 1344","1427":"1427","Trethurfe, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","England":"England","Tregothnan, Cornwall, England., United Kingdom":"Tregothnan, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Treno, Cleev, Cornwall":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Trenoweth, Cornwall, England., United